{{Top|notoc=1}}
{{Quote|Now witness the firepower of this fully armed and operational battle station.|[[Galactic Emperor|Emperor]] [[Darth Sidious|Palpatine]], to [[Luke Skywalker]]|<ref name="Episode 6">{{Film|VI}}</ref>}}
[[File:Death-Star-SWCT.png|thumb|right|250px|The first [[Death Star]] battle station]]
A '''battle station''' was any [[space station]] armed for combat. During the [[Clone Wars]], the [[Galactic Republic]] secretly began the [[Project Stardust|construction]] of the [[DS-1 Orbital Battle Station|Death Star]], a battle station unlike anything [[the galaxy]] had ever seen.<ref name="Tarkin">[[Tarkin (novel)|''Tarkin'']]</ref><ref name="Catalyst">''[[Catalyst: A Rogue One Novel]]''</ref> [[Torpedo Sphere]]s were battle stations that served as [[siege platform]]s, and were referred to as '''battlemoons'''.<ref name="Rebel Files">''[[Star Wars: The Rebel Files]]''</ref> Although it was a building, the [[Malachor Sith Temple]], or more precisely its [[Malachor superweapon|superweapon]], was also referred to as a battle station.<ref name="Twilight">{{Rebels|Twilight of the Apprentice}}</ref> The [[Starflash]] was also a superweapon used by the [[Chiss Ascendancy]].<ref name="Lesser Evil">''[[Thrawn Ascendancy: Lesser Evil]]''</ref>

